         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is the second in a series of three that analyze a method of dimensional reduction. It contains some results for approximation of functions on the interval $\lbrack -1, 1 \rbrack$ with elements from the null-space of $P^N, N \geqslant 1$, where $P$ is a second-order ordinary differential operator. A special case of this is approximation by polynomials. The one-dimensional results are used as a tool to prove similar versions in several dimensions. These multi-dimensional results are directly related to the approximate method of dimensional reduction that was introduced in [13], and they lead to statements about the convergence properties of this approach. The third paper, which analyzes the adaptive aspects of the method, is forthcoming.</p>
          </abstract>
